#Text=Wikinews interviews Rocky De La Fuente , U.S. Democratic Party presidential candidate
#Text=Thursday , March 31 , 2016
#Text=De La Fuente at the Lesser-Known Candidates Forum , January 2016 .
#Text=Image : Marc Nozell .
#Text=Businessman Rocky De La Fuente took some time to speak with Wikinews about his campaign for the U.S. Democratic Party 's 2016 presidential nomination .
#Text=The 61-year-old De La Fuente resides in San Diego , California , grew up in Tijuana , and owns multiple businesses and properties throughout the world .
#Text=Since getting his start in the automobile industry , De La Fuente has branched out into the banking and real estate markets .
#Text=Despite not having held or sought political office previously , he has been involved in politics , serving as the first-ever Hispanic superdelegate to the 1992 Democratic National Convention .
#Text=De La Fuente entered the 2016 presidential race last October largely due to his dissatisfaction with Republican front-runner Donald Trump .
#Text=He argues he is a more accomplished businessman than Trump , and attacks Trump as " a clown , " " a joke , " " dangerous , " and " in the same category as Hitler . "
#Text=Nevertheless , De La Fuente 's business background begets comparisons with Trump .
#Text=The Alaskan Midnight Sun blog described him as the Democrats ' " own Donald Trump . "

#Text=While receiving only minimal media coverage , he has campaigned actively , and according to the latest Federal Election Commission filing , loaned almost US$ 4 million of his own money to the campaign .
#Text=He has qualified for 48 primary and caucus ballots , but has not yet obtained any delegates to the 2016 Democratic National Convention .
#Text=Thus far , according to the count at The Green Papers , De La Fuente has received 35,406 votes , or 0.23 % of the total votes cast .

#Text=He leads among the many lesser-known candidates but trails both Senator Bernie Sanders who has received nearly 6.5 million votes and front-runner Hillary Clinton who has just shy of 9 million votes .
#Text=With Wikinews reporter William S. Saturn ‎ , De La Fuente discusses his personal background , his positions on political issues , his current campaign for president , and his political future .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Background
#Text=What are some of your achievements in your business career ?
#Text=From my perspective , my greatest achievements in business are tied to the people and families I have helped .
#Text=I 've had the good fortune to create dozens of business that created thousands of jobs across the United States as well as in other countries .
#Text=I always paid a fair wage , provided access to healthcare , and tried to create opportunities for advancement for those who demonstrated the desire to improve their lot in life .
#Text=Aerial view of De La Fuente 's hometown San Diego .
#Text=Image : U.S. Navy .
#Text=If you 're asking for a more traditional answer with respect to what I have personally done , at the age of twenty , I got a job selling automobiles .
#Text=Less than two years later , I became the General Manager of a dealership .
#Text=Two years after that , I acquired my first dealership and , over the next 16 years , I added 27 more dealerships to my portfolio .
#Text=And at the age of 28 , I was honored to be elected by my peers in that industry as Chairman of the National Dealer Council for the third largest Automotive Company in the world at the time .
